cord. to Az,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "intensely dark."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gaADiyapN", "text_ar": "غَاضِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Bright,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "shining brightly;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K;) applied to a night, (thus in one of my copies of the S,) or to fire ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAr", "text_ar": "نَار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "): (so in other copies of the S and in the TA:) thus having two contr. meanings. (S, K.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Great;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "applied to a fire ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nAr", "text_ar": "نار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "): a signification said by Az to be taken from the fire of the tree called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gaDFA", "text_ar": "غَضًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", which is of the best of firewood. (TA.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baEiyrN gaADK", "text_ar": "بَعِيرٌ غَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A camel that eats the trees called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gaDFA", "text_ar": "غَضًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_ibilN gaADiyapN", "text_ar": "اـِبِلٌ غَاضِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gawaADK", "text_ar": "غَوَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "camels that eat those trees"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S, K.)       -A3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aYo'N gaADK", "text_ar": "شَىْءٌ غَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A thing that is much in quantity, abundant, copious, full,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "complete."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.) ―         -b2-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rajulN gaADK", "text_ar": "رَجُلٌ غَاضٍ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A man having food and clothing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "having a good state,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "condition, in respect of food, and having clothing; sufficed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "satisfied."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Msb", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n32732", "headword_ar": "غَاضَ", "root": "gyD", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yagiyDu", "text_ar": "يَغِيضُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gayoDN", "text_ar": "غَيْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "magaADN", "text_ar": "مَغَاضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "magiyDN", "text_ar": "مَغِيضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(water)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became scanty,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "little in quantity, and sank into the earth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "disappeared in the earth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, and so in some copies of the K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became scanty,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "little in quantity, and decreased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "diminished,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became deficient:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, and so in some copies of the K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sank into the earth, and went away:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "went away into the earth;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb;) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faADa", "text_ar": "فَاضَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yafiyDu", "text_ar": "يَفِيضُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";] as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AngAD", "text_ar": "انغاض", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) which is of the dial. of El- Hijáz. (TA.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(a thing, Msb, a flow of milk, TA, and (assumed tropical:)  the price of a commodity, S, Msb, K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "decreased,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "diminished,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became deficient."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K.) ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wamaA tagiyDu A@loA^aroHaAmu wamaA", "text_ar": "وَمَا تَغِيضُ ا@لْاَرْحَامُ وَمَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tazodaAdu", "text_ar": "تَزْدَادُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, * K, * TA,) in the Kur [xiii. 9], (S,) means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And the wombs' falling short"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of completion"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of what is usual"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (Akh, S, Bd,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and their exceeding"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "therein"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in respect of the body"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the fœtus"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and the period of gestation, and the number borne:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Bd:) or, as some say,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in respect"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2317}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the menstrual blood:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Bd:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the wombs' falling short of the nine months"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, O, L, and so in copies of the K, but in others"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "seven months,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of gestation, and their exceeding the nine"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "seven"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "months:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, O, L:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the wombs' falling short of completion, so that the fœtus dies, and their exceeding so that the gestation becomes complete:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and accord. to this explanation, the reading of seven months in the K may be correct: see also Katádeh's explanation of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gayoDN", "text_ar": "غَيْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", below, which favours this reading. (TA.) ―         -b4-  You say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gaADa AlkiraAmu wafaADa All~iy^aAmu", "text_ar": "غَاضَ الكِرَامُ وَفَاضَ اللِّيَامُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A) (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The generous became few,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, TA,) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "failed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "perished,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and the mean became many."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gaADahu", "text_ar": "غَاضَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, K,) aor. as above, inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gayoDN", "text_ar": "غَيْضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(God, S, Msb)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "made it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(i. e. water)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to become scanty,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "little in quantity, and to sink into the earth,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "disappear in the earth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "made it to decrease,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "diminish,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "become deficient:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "made it to go away into the earth:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb:) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AgADhu", "text_ar": "اغاضهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies the same; (S, A, K;) and so does ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gy~Dhu", "text_ar": "غيّضهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tagoyiyDN", "text_ar": "تَغْيِيضٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) thus the first of these verbs is trans. as well as intrans. (S.) [It is said in the Kur xi. 46,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wagiyDa A@lomaA='u", "text_ar": "وَغِيضَ ا@لْمَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And the water was made to become scanty,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.: (S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "was made to decrease,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "diminish."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, * Bd.) And hence the saying of 'Áïsheh, describing her father,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wagaADa naboEa Alr~id~api", "text_ar": "وَغَاضَ نَبْعَ الرِّدَّةِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And he did away with what appeared of apostacy."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) You say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "damoEahu", "text_ar": "دَمْعَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gy~D", "text_ar": "غيّض", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, * K,) inf. n. as above, (K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He made his tears to diminish,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and restrained them:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he took the tears from his eye and dashed them away."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Th.) A poet says, (TA,) namely, Jereer, (O and TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gbD", "text_ar": "غبض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",)"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "mino EabaraAtihin~a waqulona liY ↓ \n      gay~aDona\n                      \n                     \n                        maA *aA laqiyta mina AlhawaY walaqiynaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They made their tears to flow until they exhausted them"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and they said to me, What is it that thou hast experienced, of love, and we have experienced?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: ISd says that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mn", "text_ar": "من"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "here denotes some; or it may be redundant, accord. to the opinion of Abu-l-Hasan; for he holds that it may be so in affirmative [as well as negative] phrases, mentioning, as an instance,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qado kaAna mino", "text_ar": "قَدْ كَانَ مِنْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maTarK", "text_ar": "مَطَرٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qado kaAna maTarN", "text_ar": "قَدْ كَانَ مَطَرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) One relation of this verse gives"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gab~aDona", "text_ar": "غَبَّضْنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; but the former is the right. (O and TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gbD", "text_ar": "غبض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He opened a way, passage,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "channel, for it"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(namely water)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to flow forth to a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "magiyD", "text_ar": "مَغِيض"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]. (Msb.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He diminished it,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "namely the price of a commodity; (Ks, S, Msb, K;) as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AgADhu", "text_ar": "اغاضهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (K.) ―         -b4-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He caused him to suffer loss,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "detriment;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wronged,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "injured, him."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(ISd, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "A", "Msb", "K", "TA", "Akh", "Bd", "Zj", "O", "L", "God"]}]}, "classical_definitions": {"source": "hawramani", "url": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%BA%D8%A7%D8%B6/", "headword_ar": "غَاضّ", "entries": [{"lexicon_id": "dictionary_48", "lexicon_en": "Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)", "lexicon_ar": "موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب", "permalink": "https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=104988#fc112b", "body_html": "غَاضّ<br>من (غ ض ض) الذي يكف بصره أو صوته أو يحفظهما."}]}, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}